As for Mr. Lavelle...I know him.  Well.  He is one of the most honorable men I have ever met, who's values time and time again reflect forethought for his fellow man.  It's kind of funny really.  I am engaged to be married to a retired Naval Chief...also one of the most honorable men I have ever known.  I read these posts...and look at the moaning and groaning about who's right and who's wrong...and I wonder if you're ramblings have helped, even remotely, to dry the tears of a mother who has lost her son to the Viet Nam war...knowing that he died for what he believed in, and supporting him in that decision.  It is so unfortunate, &quot;Mr&quot; Spatz, that you cannot see that you, personally, are not what's most important in this scenario!
